#: ../../../reference/arrays.dtypes.rst:535
msgid "Checking the data type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/arrays.dtypes.rst:536
msgid "When checking for a specific data type, use ``==`` comparison."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/arrays.dtypes.rst:548
msgid ""
"As opposed to Python types, a comparison using ``is`` should not be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/arrays.dtypes.rst:550
msgid ""
"First, NumPy treats data type specifications (everything that can be passed "
"to the :class:`dtype` constructor) as equivalent to the data type object "
"itself. This equivalence can only be handled through ``==``, not through "
"``is``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/arrays.dtypes.rst:558
msgid ""
"A :class:`dtype` object is equal to all data type specifications that are "
